The paper deals with machine learning methods for classification of Alzheimer's disease using MRI and PET data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also involves feature extraction and classification algorithms, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the classification methods in the context of Alzheimer's disease, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
